---
import BaseLayout from '@/components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About Moe Qadan"
  description="Senior UX and frontend practitioner in Los Angeles. Currently leading web experience at MagTek. Shipping ChatOBD2 solo. Previously deployed advisor portals at InvestCloud across 50+ wealth and banking institutions."
  keywords={[
    'Moe Qadan',
    'about',
    'UX engineer',
    'senior frontend',
    'web experience',
    'design systems',
    'background',
    'experience',
  ]}
>
  <div class="about">
    <div class="about__hero">
      <div class="container-site">
        <span class="about__eyebrow">About</span>
        <h1 class="about__title">
          Moe Qadan
        </h1>
        <p class="about__hero-sub">
          Senior UX and frontend practitioner based in Los Angeles. I
          do the parts of web work that usually get split across a
          team. Most days that's the seam where Figma, the codebase,
          the content model, the SEO graph, and the performance budget
          all have to agree.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container-site about__body">
      <div class="about__prose">
        <h2 class="about__h2">What I'm best at</h2>
        <p class="about__para">
          The work I get hired for tends to fall into a few shapes.
        </p>
        <ul class="about__bullets">
          <li><strong>Owning the whole web experience for a team that doesn't have a department for it.</strong> UX, design system, frontend, content architecture, SEO, performance, accessibility, all on one person.</li>
          <li><strong>Modernizing platforms that can't be rewritten.</strong> Long-running systems with traffic on them, opinions baked in, integrations the business depends on. The win is incremental, sequenced, and invisible when it lands.</li>
          <li><strong>Building component systems engineers actually use.</strong> Typed, documented, scoped, migrated to without flag days. Right now it's a 100+ component Razor partial library at MagTek; previously it was per-tenant CSS systems on InvestCloud's framework across more than 50 institutions.</li>
          <li><strong>Translating design intent into code at fidelity.</strong> Reading what the file is asking for, not just what it specifies, and closing the gaps a handoff doesn't see. Most production breakage lives in those gaps.</li>
          <li><strong>Shipping AI-assisted features without the buzzword tax.</strong> Prompts as system rather than scattered components. Schema-bound outputs. The model held as one stage in a pipeline. ChatOBD2 is the worked example.</li>
        </ul>

        <hr class="about__rule" />

        <h2 class="about__h2">Background</h2>

        <ol class="about__career">
          <li class="about__career-item about__career-item--current">
            <header class="about__career-head">
              <span class="about__career-status">Current</span>
              <h3 class="about__career-title">ChatOBD2</h3>
              <span class="about__career-period">2025, present</span>
            </header>
            <p class="about__career-desc">
              Founder, sole designer and engineer. AI-native automotive
              diagnostics product I built end to end: mobile app,
              marketing site, developer portal, prompt pipeline. The
              design problem was translation. Vehicle data is messy and
              technical; the verdict has to be a single sentence the
              driver can act on.
            </p>
            <p class="about__career-stack">
              React Native (Expo), TypeScript, Supabase, BLE, structured
              prompt pipeline, Next.js + Tailwind for the marketing site.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li class="about__career-item about__career-item--current">
            <header class="about__career-head">
              <span class="about__career-status">Current</span>
              <h3 class="about__career-title">MagTek</h3>
              <span class="about__career-period">Now</span>
            </header>
            <p class="about__career-desc">
              I lead the web experience across MagTek.com, Magensa, the
              hardware product line, the support portal, and the network
              of related properties built on the shared ASP.NET MVC
              substrate. The work is platform-level: a 100+ component
              Razor partial library, a CSS foundation rebuilt as design
              tokens, navigation grammar that travels, sequenced
              migrations that don't break production.
            </p>
            <p class="about__career-stack">
              ASP.NET MVC, C#, Razor, hand-authored CSS, JavaScript,
              Bootstrap.
            </p>
          </li>

          <li class="about__career-item">
            <header class="about__career-head">
              <span class="about__career-status">Past</span>
              <h3 class="about__career-title">InvestCloud</h3>
              <span class="about__career-period">Earlier</span>
            </header>
            <p class="about__career-desc">
              Contributed to or led 0-to-production deploys for advisor
              and customer portals across <strong>50+ wealth-management and
              banking institutions</strong>: Chase, Cetera, Northwestern
              Mutual, Voya, Silicon Valley Bank, East West Bank, and
              many more. Multi-tenant frontend, per-institution branding,
              dense data layouts, and the discipline that comes from
              fifty deploys against the same substrate.
            </p>
            <p class="about__career-stack">
              CSS, proprietary CMS / component framework, Figma handoff
              translation.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <hr class="about__rule" />

        <h2 class="about__h2">How I think about the work</h2>

        <p class="about__para">
          A few things I keep coming back to.
        </p>

        <ol class="about__list">
          <li>
            <strong>Read the constraints first.</strong> Long-running platforms
            have opinions about how they want to be changed. Listening
            to them is how the work survives.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Get the structure right early.</strong> Components,
            tokens, layout primitives, content models. When those are
            sound most decisions become cheap. When they aren't every
            decision is expensive.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Use AI where it earns its place.</strong> Code in
            Claude or Cursor when it's faster than typing. Visual
            exploration in Claude Design when a frame is faster than
            markup. Figma when precision matters.
          </li>
        </ol>

        <p class="about__para about__para--note">
          More on the workflow itself, including how AI fits into the
          build pipeline, lives on the
          <a href="/approach" class="about__inline-link">approach</a> page.
        </p>
      </div>

      <aside class="about__aside">
        <div class="about__card">
          <h3 class="about__card-title">Currently</h3>
          <ul class="about__card-list">
            <li>
              <span class="about__card-key">Status</span>
              <span class="about__card-val about__card-val--status">
                <span class="about__card-status-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                Open to projects
              </span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="about__card-key">Best fit</span>
              <span class="about__card-val">UX + frontend as one job. Design systems. AI-native product work. Long-running platforms.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="about__card-key">Building</span>
              <span class="about__card-val">ChatOBD2 · MagTek platform</span>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="about__card-key">Stack</span>
              <span class="about__card-val">TypeScript · React · React Native · Astro · ASP.NET MVC · C# · Razor · hand-authored CSS</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="about__card">
          <h3 class="about__card-title">Reach out</h3>
          <p class="about__card-note">
            Tell me what you're building. Reply within a day.
          </p>
          <a href="/contact" class="about__card-cta">
            Get in touch
            <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M3 8h10M9 4l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about__hero {
    padding-top: calc(60px + var(--space-10));
    padding-bottom: var(--space-10);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-10);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .about__hero {
      padding-top: calc(64px + var(--space-16));
      padding-bottom: var(--space-12);
      margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    }
  }

  .about__eyebrow {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about__title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(40px, 9.5vw, 80px);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    line-height: 1.05;
    color: var(--color-text);
    max-width: 18ch;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .about__hero-sub {
    font-size: clamp(16px, 1.7vw, 19px);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    max-width: 62ch;
  }

  .about__body {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-10);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-16);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .about__body {
      gap: var(--space-12);
      padding-bottom: var(--space-24);
    }
  }

  @media (min-width: 1024px) {
    .about__body {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 320px;
      gap: var(--space-16);
    }
  }

  .about__para {
    font-size: clamp(15px, 1.5vw, 17px);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .about__para--note {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    line-height: 1.65;
    padding: var(--space-3) var(--space-4);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-muted);
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
  }

  .about__inline-link {
    color: var(--color-text);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-border);
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    transition: color 150ms, text-decoration-color 150ms;
  }

  .about__inline-link:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .about__bullets {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-6);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    max-width: 64ch;
  }

  .about__bullets li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 24px;
    font-size: clamp(15px, 1.5vw, 17px);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .about__bullets li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.7em;
    width: 12px;
    height: 1px;
    background-color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .about__bullets strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .about__rule {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    margin: var(--space-12) 0 var(--space-10);
  }

  .about__h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(24px, 2.8vw, 34px);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  /* Career timeline */
  .about__career {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .about__career-item {
    padding: var(--space-5);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  @media (min-width: 600px) {
    .about__career-item {
      padding: var(--space-6) var(--space-7);
    }
  }

  .about__career-item--current {
    border-color: var(--color-accent-muted);
    background-image: radial-gradient(ellipse 50% 80% at 100% 0%, var(--color-accent-dim), transparent 65%);
  }

  .about__career-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .about__career-status {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    padding: 3px 8px;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    background-color: var(--color-bg-muted);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .about__career-item--current .about__career-status {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    background-color: var(--color-accent-dim);
    border-color: var(--color-accent-muted);
  }

  .about__career-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(22px, 2.4vw, 28px);
    font-weight: 400;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin: 0;
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .about__career-period {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }

  .about__career-desc {
    font-size: clamp(14px, 1.4vw, 16px);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  .about__career-desc strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .about__career-stack {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin: 0;
    padding-top: var(--space-3);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border-subtle);
  }

  .about__list {
    counter-reset: about-list;
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .about__list li {
    counter-increment: about-list;
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 36px;
    font-size: clamp(15px, 1.5vw, 17px);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    max-width: 62ch;
  }

  .about__list li::before {
    content: counter(about-list, decimal-leading-zero);
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 4px;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }

  .about__list strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* Sidebar */
  .about__aside {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about__card {
    padding: var(--space-5);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated);
  }

  .about__card-title {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about__card-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .about__card-list li {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2px;
  }

  .about__card-key {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-text-subtle);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }

  .about__card-val {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.45;
  }

  .about__card-val--status {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 7px;
    color: var(--color-success);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }

  .about__card-status-dot {
    width: 7px;
    height: 7px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background-color: var(--color-success);
    box-shadow: 0 0 8px color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-success) 65%, transparent);
    animation: about-status-pulse 2.4s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  @keyframes about-status-pulse {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 1; transform: scale(1); }
    50% { opacity: 0.7; transform: scale(0.85); }
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .about__card-status-dot { animation: none; }
  }

  .about__card-note {
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about__card-cta {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-bottom: 4px;
    transition: color 150ms, border-color 150ms;
  }

  .about__card-cta:hover {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    border-bottom-color: var(--color-accent);
  }
</style>
